    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-05-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="337"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <head>337. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d337fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, INR/IL Historical Files, Latin America
                        General, 1969–70. Secret.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d337fn2">During its regular weekly meeting
                        with the Department of State, <gloss target="#CIA1">CIA</gloss> indicated
                        concerns over the possibility of U.S. Government help to President-elect
                            <persName corresp="#p_AOC1">Arana</persName> to deal with internal
                        security problems, fearing that the new government would indulge in
                        counter-terror.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-05-08">May 8, 1970</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d337-1" n="1" xml:id="pg_d337-1"/>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT:</head>
                    <item>Regular Weekly Meeting with Department of State, 8 May 1970</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PRESENT:</head>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CJH1">John H. Crimmins</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HRA1">Robert A. Hurwitch</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GJR1">James R. Gardner</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BWV1">William V. Broe</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. John R. Horton</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to Guatemala.]</p>
                <pb facs="d337-2" n="2" xml:id="pg_d337-2"/>
                <p>Guatemala</p>
                <p>11. The ambassador has directed that the Public Safety element [<hi rend="italic"
                        >text not declassified</hi>] be ready to help President-elect <persName
                        corresp="#p_AOC1">Arana</persName> in dealing with internal security
                    problems if he asks for such help on coming into office. [<hi rend="italic">text
                        not declassified</hi>] the dismal history [<hi rend="italic">text not
                        declassified</hi>] trying to make something out of the security service,
                    largely owing to the sort of Guatemalan who has been assigned to security work.
                    In addition, CIA fears that the new government will indulge in counterterror
                        [<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>] Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJH1">Crimmins</persName> thought that the counterterror
                    campaign had at one time led us to pull out our Public Safety mission but [<hi
                        rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>] The U.S. mission had tried for a
                    long time to get the Guatemalans to staff and properly run an operations center
                    but that this scheme never got off the ground. [<hi rend="italic">text not
                        declassified</hi>]</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to Guatemala.]</p>
            </div>
